1
00:00:03,749 --> 00:00:06,641
What does Kṛṣṇa say
in the Bhagavad-gītā?

2
00:00:06,641 --> 00:00:09,834
Again He says, “Are you going 
to do this analysis

3
00:00:09,834 --> 00:00:12,991
or take advantage of the analysis
of revealed truth?”

4
00:00:13,021 --> 00:00:16,541
[Freedom For / From the Senses]

5
00:00:16,834 --> 00:00:21,852
So, we try to come under the influence
of the revealed truth.

6
00:00:21,852 --> 00:00:24,363
We say, “Oh,
in Bhagavad-gītā Kṛṣṇa says,

7
00:00:24,363 --> 00:00:29,403
‘Above the objects of the senses
are the senses’;

8
00:00:29,403 --> 00:00:32,689
they’re higher, refined,
they’re superior.

9
00:00:32,689 --> 00:00:36,246
‘But above the senses
is the mind.’

10
00:00:36,307 --> 00:00:38,869
Okay, the mind is
higher than the senses,

11
00:00:38,869 --> 00:00:41,238
and it’s the seat 
of sense experience.”

12
00:00:41,238 --> 00:00:44,421
Then He says, “Finer than the mind
is intelligence.”

13
00:00:44,421 --> 00:00:47,558
Then we say, “Okay, now I
understand, intelligence—

14
00:00:47,558 --> 00:00:51,150
the discriminating factor because
the mind has no discriminating ability.”

15
00:00:51,160 --> 00:00:54,459
So, we’re told, you need to infuse
the intelligence with dharma-buddhi,

16
00:00:54,459 --> 00:00:56,837
back to
sādhu, sāstra, guru, Vaiṣṇav.

17
00:00:56,837 --> 00:00:59,723
Finer than intelligence,
He’s saying, is what?

18
00:00:59,723 --> 00:01:02,950
“That’s the beginning 
of the ātma plane.”

19
00:01:02,950 --> 00:01:06,268
So that’s where
the self is located.

20
00:01:06,268 --> 00:01:11,532
So if you are viewing the self
from the outside in

21
00:01:11,532 --> 00:01:20,350
and seeing yourself in terms of gender,
nationality, age, all of these things,

22
00:01:20,350 --> 00:01:25,236
you’re not having
a proper glimpse of yourself,

23
00:01:25,236 --> 00:01:29,353
and who you are,
and what is your potential.

24
00:01:29,353 --> 00:01:32,284
How can you proceed?

25
00:01:33,715 --> 00:01:39,448
So you have people thinking
the most important aspect of their lives

26
00:01:39,448 --> 00:01:43,208
is their sexuality; 
that’s who they are,

27
00:01:43,208 --> 00:01:45,582
and they need
to express their sexuality,

28
00:01:45,582 --> 00:01:47,892
and then they’ll be free,
they’ll be liberated,

29
00:01:47,892 --> 00:01:50,686
they’ll live a life
of freedom and happiness

30
00:01:50,686 --> 00:01:56,141
by identifying with
a particular aspect of sexuality.

31
00:01:58,232 --> 00:02:01,269
I mean I’m not making this up.

32
00:02:01,854 --> 00:02:05,507
So they think, “That’s freedom,
freedom to express yourself”,

33
00:02:05,507 --> 00:02:15,115
that, “I profess this type of
sexual preference, now I’m a liberated soul,

34
00:02:15,574 --> 00:02:21,373
and I want to be viewed exclusively
in terms of my sexuality.”

35
00:02:22,387 --> 00:02:24,277
So then
we have to consider:

36
00:02:24,277 --> 00:02:26,844
What is freedom? 
What is liberation?

37
00:02:26,844 --> 00:02:29,705
Well, Guru Mahārāj , as usual,
put it in the proper terms,

38
00:02:29,705 --> 00:02:35,041
“Freedom for the senses,
or freedom from the senses?”

39
00:02:35,087 --> 00:02:37,792
Most people would think, “No,
it means freedom for the senses,

40
00:02:37,792 --> 00:02:40,319
to do what you want.”

41
00:02:40,688 --> 00:02:44,708
So should we say that someone,
who’s under the influence,

42
00:02:44,708 --> 00:02:48,036
in the language of the scripture
‘vācho vegaṁ manasa’—

43
00:02:48,036 --> 00:02:52,835
the belly, tongue, and genitals,
they’re engaged in self-expression?

44
00:02:52,850 --> 00:02:58,668
That’s a liberated position!
—Really?

45
00:03:00,299 --> 00:03:03,028
That the tongue wants to eat this,

46
00:03:03,028 --> 00:03:07,911
so I allow the tongue to drag me
in a direction, that’s freedom?

47
00:03:07,926 --> 00:03:10,979
“I’m expressing who I am.”

48
00:03:11,779 --> 00:03:15,490
I remember when I was a teenager,
and I’d become a vegetarian,

49
00:03:15,490 --> 00:03:18,790
and a friend of mine—we’re having
this discussion back and forth—

50
00:03:18,790 --> 00:03:22,617
and he’s like, 
“Oh, why are you doing this?”

51
00:03:22,648 --> 00:03:25,261
And at the time for me
it was an intuitive thing,

52
00:03:25,261 --> 00:03:29,886
it wasn’t based upon 
a lot of analytical thought,

53
00:03:29,886 --> 00:03:32,886
it was just 
an intuitive compulsion.

54
00:03:32,886 --> 00:03:38,052
But he was starting to feel defensive
about eating meat,

55
00:03:38,129 --> 00:03:41,942
so he once said to me,
“When I eat a steak,

56
00:03:41,942 --> 00:03:47,189
it’s an expression
of my love for the cow.”

57
00:03:47,189 --> 00:03:50,903
We were in a band, and the lead guitarist
turned to him and said,

58
00:03:50,903 --> 00:03:53,276
“That’s total bullshit.”

59
00:03:53,276 --> 00:03:57,472
Like, “Do you expect us 
to believe that?”

60
00:03:57,566 --> 00:04:08,456
Even he, who was not a vegetarian,
thought it was an absurd denial.

61
00:04:08,472 --> 00:04:13,871
He said, “It’s an expression
of my love for the cow”;

62
00:04:13,917 --> 00:04:17,455
I go, “You should be careful 
who you love,

63
00:04:17,470 --> 00:04:24,008
or those whom you love
should be careful in dealing with you.”

